Package org.loboevolution.html.js.geolocation

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Coordinates
    The CoordinatesImpl class provides Java implementation of the "CoordinatesImpl Interface" as detailed out in the W3C Specifications (http://www.w3.org/TR/geolocation-API/#coordinates_interface) Note: This class must not have any sub-classes to ensure W3C Specifications are being strictly followed by the system or application that uses this geolocation package.
    Geolocation
    The Geolocation class provides Java implementation of the "Geolocation Interface" as detailed out in the W3C Specifications ( http://www.w3.org/TR/geolocation-API/#geolocation_interface).
    IPAddressBasedGeoAcquirer
    IPAddressBasedGeoAcquirer class.
    Position
    he Position class provides Java implementation of the "Position Interface" as detailed out in the W3C Specifications (http://www.w3.org/TR/geolocation-API/#position).
    PositionError
    The PositionError class provides a way to provide error when the position cannot be calculated due to any reason.
    PositionOptions
    The PositionOptions class provides a way for the application to set options that the Geolocation object can then use when calculating the position.
